    "refcode_long": "Counsels on Sabbath School Work, p. 179.3 (Ellen Gould White)",
    "element_type": "p",
    "element_subtype": "standard-indented",
    "content": "If Christ is abiding in his [the teacher&apos;s] heart by faith, sin appears revolting. While he will have love, kindness, and tenderness for the scholars under his charge, he will feel that as a faithful servant he must discipline and preserve order in his class. If truth is cherished, the love of the Saviour is revealed in <span class=\"page-break\" data-page=\"180\"></span> his words and deportment. The word of God with him is not a dead letter; he will give not only lip service, but heart service.&mdash;<span class=\"egwlink egwlink_book\" title=\"TSS 25.1\" data-link=\"121.90\"><em>Testimonies on Sabbath-School Work</em>, 25, 26</span>,",
